	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've got a question about macros, and I'd like to have my understanding checked.<br />Does a macro have this format:<br />.macro &lt;name&gt; &lt;parameters&gt;<br />&lt;code&gt;<br />.endmacro<br />(or equivalents)<br />and is it called like this:<br />.macroname &lt;parameters&gt;<br />Furthermore, does the assembler inline the macro code wherever the macro is called?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

