	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Macros replace the text before doing any assembly, so yes this is kind of like &quot;inline&quot;.<br /><br />I presume you're asking about ca65 but you didn't specify. Here's the manual page for macros, it has examples that should answer your questions:<br /><a href="http://www.cc65.org/doc/ca65-12.html" class="postlink">http://www.cc65.org/doc/ca65-12.html</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


